        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3588045038" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1510641518654340773"><b>4.5 Stars</b><br/><br/>I&apos;m having a hard time thinking about what I want to say here, but I want to get something down before this review ends up in the &quot;review to come&quot; abyss, never to be seen or heard from again. The irony there, right? <br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1602527212ra/30228592.gif' width='500' height='278' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Anyway...<br/><br/>I LOVED this book. Especially the first 220 pages. <br/><br/>Schwab&apos;s writing was superb. I actually have two complete series by her on my shelves and have yet to finish a single book by her...I&apos;m hoping I didn&apos;t set myself up for constant disappoint here by making my first f</span>
  <span id="freeText1510641518654340773" style="display:none"><b>4.5 Stars</b><br><br>I'm having a hard time thinking about what I want to say here, but I want to get something down before this review ends up in the "review to come" abyss, never to be seen or heard from again. The irony there, right? <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1602527212ra/30228592.gif" width="500" height="278" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Anyway...<br><br>I LOVED this book. Especially the first 220 pages. <br><br>Schwab's writing was superb. I actually have two complete series by her on my shelves and have yet to finish a single book by her...I'm hoping I didn't set myself up for constant disappoint here by making my first finish by her be her best. <br><br>But I digress. The writing. <br><br>Soooooo good. Truly. I am not a fan of purple prose, really. And while I don't necessarily think this was full on purple, it was definitely poignant and almost lyrical at times. Schwab has a way of describing things that makes them tangible. Something unique and yet very everyone at the same time. <br><br>And Addie...<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1602534260i/30228978.jpg" width="400" height="224" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>What a character. I just adored her and her story. Especially, as I said, the first 220 pages of it. After that...well, that's were that -.5 star comes in, I suppose. Without giving spoilers, I will just say that the tone and haunting quality of the story changed a little bit when Henry arrived on scene. And I couldn't help but feel that something had been lost even though I know we, along with Addie, were supposed to feel like something had been gained.<br><br>Or maybe that was the point. <br><br>Before starting this, I had an idea of how things would end...and I was actually right. I just didn't know I would enjoy how things would <i>go</i> so much. But I think the journey is perhaps the point, isn't it? <br><br>Anyway, I don't want to give anything away, so I will stop here. <br>Some things are better left open-ended, no?</span>
